Dad, what's going on?

27:55.632 --> 27:57.373
Charley, get the fuck
back in your room.

27:57.968 --> 27:58.799
Shit.

27:58.886 --> 28:00.468
Come in. Come in.

28:00.554 --> 28:03.262
Calm down. Calm down. Maybe I can help.

28:03.348 --> 28:04.884
You wanna talk about it?
I'll get you a beer.

28:04.975 --> 28:07.183
We should have a beer together.
Just stop. Shh.

28:07.728 --> 28:08.559
Fuck you.

28:08.645 --> 28:09.761
Dad!

28:14.151 --> 28:17.235
Stop it! Get off... Charley!

28:24.870 --> 28:26.987
Oh...

28:43.680 --> 28:45.672
You okay? You okay?

28:47.184 --> 28:49.096
Okay...

28:49.186 --> 28:51.644
Okay, okay, okay...

28:51.897 --> 28:53.229
Call 911!

28:54.191 --> 28:56.057
It's gonna be okay. It's gonna be okay.

28:56.777 --> 28:59.019
Okay, I'm gonna be right back, okay? Okay.

29:00.197 --> 29:02.063
Call 911, please!

29:03.033 --> 29:04.524
My dad is really hurt!

29:06.578 --> 29:08.695
It's gonna be okay. It's gonna be okay.

29:09.248 --> 29:11.365
No, no, no...

29:14.419 --> 29:16.331
- Where are they taking him?
- To Samaritan.

29:16.838 --> 29:18.625
- Is he gonna be okay?
- Why don't we get out of the road?

29:18.715 --> 29:19.956
Can you tell us what happened tonight?

29:20.467 --> 29:21.503
I don't know.

29:21.969 --> 29:24.461
I was just asleep,
and this guy started beating on the door,

29:24.554 --> 29:25.590
and he broke the lock.

29:25.847 --> 29:26.837
Do you know his name?

29:27.391 --> 29:28.347
No.

29:28.433 --> 29:32.347
But my dad was seeing this lady,
and she was married to this Samoan.

29:32.437 --> 29:33.644
And what's her name?

29:33.730 --> 29:35.471
Um, Lynn.

29:36.358 --> 29:37.894
- I don't know her last name.
- How old are you?

29:38.277 --> 29:39.313
I'm 15.

29:40.028 --> 29:41.644
Do you have someone
to look after you tonight?

29:44.700 --> 29:45.861
My aunt's coming.

29:46.743 --> 29:47.733
Are you sure?

29:48.328 --> 29:49.944
Yeah, she's on her way right now.

29:50.747 --> 29:51.954
All right. Wait here a minute.

29:52.457 --> 29:53.447
We'll be right back.

29:55.168 --> 29:56.375
We should call Family Services.

29:57.212 --> 29:59.044
Give me the number, I can call them.

30:30.579 --> 30:32.787
<i>So, your dad
just got out of surgery,</i>

30:32.873 --> 30:34.330
<i>so he's gonna look a little bit messed up.</i>

30:34.875 --> 30:37.583
<i>The glass actually ended up
cutting his bowels,</i>

30:37.669 --> 30:39.877
<i>so it seeped an infection into his gut.</i>

30:40.589 --> 30:42.376
- Is that serious?
- Yes.

30:43.008 --> 30:45.500
It's very serious.
It's like he's been poisoned.

31:00.859 --> 31:02.350
Okay, I'm gonna leave you two alone.

31:03.028 --> 31:05.645
Just try not too much talking...

31:05.739 --> 31:07.401
...your dad needs to rest.

31:09.451 --> 31:10.441
Hey.

31:11.995 --> 31:12.985
Does it hurt?

31:14.206 --> 31:15.196
No.

31:15.874 --> 31:17.957
They got me pretty doped up.

31:24.216 --> 31:25.206
You're gonna be okay?

31:27.886 --> 31:28.876
I hope so.

31:35.310 --> 31:37.097
Do you think he's gonna come back?

31:37.854 --> 31:39.686
No. He won't be back.

31:42.442 --> 31:43.853
Big fucker.

31:45.654 --> 31:46.644
Yeah.

31:47.948 --> 31:50.440
He's the biggest guy I've ever seen.

31:53.578 --> 31:54.989
I'm sorry...

31:56.540 --> 31:59.453
that he threw you
through the door like that.

31:59.876 --> 32:00.866
Hey.

32:02.045 --> 32:03.035
I'm gonna be fine.

32:05.048 --> 32:07.916
- You should go home. Get some sleep.
- Mmm. No, no.

32:08.552 --> 32:09.884
I'm gonna stay right here, okay?

32:12.264 --> 32:15.974
- I'm not gonna be much company.
- I'm gonna stay right here.

32:16.768 --> 32:18.725
- It's okay.
- Yeah.

32:19.062 --> 32:20.553
- Okay?
- Yeah.

32:21.022 --> 32:22.103
I'm gonna stay right here.

32:26.153 --> 32:27.360
Okay.

32:29.656 --> 32:30.567
Okay.

33:06.776 --> 33:07.766
Hey, Dad.

33:08.904 --> 33:12.739
Do you think you could give me
the number for Aunt Margy?

33:17.370 --> 33:18.406
Why?

33:18.497 --> 33:20.784
Well, just so I could call her.

33:22.667 --> 33:26.536
I think... maybe she could help right now.

33:33.094 --> 33:35.256
We can take care of ourselves.

33:37.599 --> 33:38.510
You and me.

33:38.767 --> 33:40.099
We don't need anyone's help.

33:44.147 --> 33:45.137
No, I know.

33:47.567 --> 33:48.557
But...

33:49.778 --> 33:51.189
with you being here and...

33:52.405 --> 33:55.944
me being back home, uh...

33:58.870 --> 34:00.782
You know what you need to do?

34:03.166 --> 34:06.000
You need to go home,
get a good night's sleep.

34:09.714 --> 34:12.252
You're the only one working, you know.
We need that money.

34:12.342 --> 34:15.130
I ain't gonna get shit being laid up.

34:17.429 --> 34:18.545
So, it's up to you.

34:25.730 --> 34:26.719
Okay.

36:29.688 --> 36:30.678
Hey, buddy.

36:31.481 --> 36:32.471
Just me.

36:34.818 --> 36:35.808
Hey.

36:37.487 --> 36:40.730
I'm gonna be staying next door
for a little while until Dad gets better.

36:45.161 --> 36:46.652
Promise not to tell Del.

36:47.872 --> 36:49.704
You know he wouldn't like it much.

36:52.711 --> 36:54.418
It's gonna be fun, 'cause I'm gonna...

36:54.963 --> 36:56.545
get to come visit you a lot more.

37:04.764 --> 37:05.550
No, I understand,

37:05.640 --> 37:07.677
but can you tell him
that I'll be away for the night,

37:07.767 --> 37:09.099
but that I'll be back tomorrow?

37:09.185 --> 37:11.723
- <i>Sure, I'll tell him.</i>
- Now you promise you'll tell him that?

37:11.813 --> 37:13.475
<i>Yes, I promise I'll tell him.</i>

37:14.023 --> 37:15.139
<i>He's doing fine.</i>

37:15.233 --> 37:16.269
- Okay.
<i>- Don't worry.</i>

37:17.110 --> 37:18.066
Yeah, thank you very much.

37:18.153 --> 37:19.815
Charley, hurry the fuck up!

37:19.904 --> 37:20.985
All right, you too. Thank you.

37:23.074 --> 37:25.191
There she is.

37:30.290 --> 37:31.280
Move over.

37:32.208 --> 37:33.198
Get in the front.

37:38.381 --> 37:39.371
Hey.

37:40.300 --> 37:41.290
This is Charley.

37:41.718 --> 37:43.926
- Hey, Charley, I'm Bonnie.
- Are you a jockey?

37:44.429 --> 37:46.011
She's too fat
to be a real jockey.

37:46.097 --> 37:49.181
Ugh, I just lost seven pounds.
I'm down to 122.

37:49.601 --> 37:50.432
Yeah?

37:50.518 --> 37:52.134
I swear to God.
Get a fucking scale right now.

37:52.228 --> 37:53.264
Oh yeah, okay.

38:04.032 --> 38:05.398
<i>So, what
do you like to do, Charley?</i>

38:05.492 --> 38:07.734
<i>When Del here isn't making you do
all his dirty work?</i>

38:07.827 --> 38:10.695
- <i>I run. I play football.
- At school?</i>

38:10.789 --> 38:12.496
Yeah. But not yet.

38:12.832 --> 38:15.495
I played in Spokane.
I was on the freshman team.

38:16.419 --> 38:17.785
We won eight games in a row.

38:18.588 --> 38:19.578
What position?

38:20.173 --> 38:22.460
Corner. And sometimes wide receiver.

38:23.218 --> 38:25.710
But... I'm too little
to play anything else.

38:28.431 --> 38:30.923
I'm waiting to lift weights
until I stop growing.

38:32.227 --> 38:36.346
I haven't grown in six months, so...
maybe soon.

38:38.107 --> 38:39.268
Why did you move to Portland?

38:40.777 --> 38:42.393
My dad moved here for work.

38:44.113 --> 38:46.230
- What does he do?
- Can we not talk?

38:47.408 --> 38:48.819
I ain't talking to you.
I'm talking to the kid.

38:49.911 --> 38:52.824
I was tired of talking to you 15 minutes
after I met you 20 years ago.

38:56.251 --> 38:57.241
That's a good one.

38:58.211 --> 38:59.327
Just tell it like I see it.

39:24.737 --> 39:26.854
<i>Is it hard being a girl jockey?</i>

39:27.073 --> 39:28.735
It isn't easy, that's for sure.

39:29.409 --> 39:32.072
I used to work out horses up at the track
for a couple of trainers.

39:32.370 --> 39:33.781
They always promised me rides.

39:33.872 --> 39:36.239
And then when it came time,
never called my name.

39:36.916 --> 39:39.533
So, I just had to wait around
for the horses no one else wanted to ride.

39:40.753 --> 39:41.743
Did you ever get hurt?

39:42.672 --> 39:46.040
Yeah, once at a race in Union,
which is way out in Eastern Oregon,

39:46.134 --> 39:47.124
I was in the gate,

39:47.343 --> 39:49.130
this horse reared up,
flipped over backwards,

39:49.220 --> 39:50.210
and I couldn't get out.

39:50.430 --> 39:51.420
He landed on me.

39:52.223 --> 39:54.636
- What happened?
- Broke my pelvis, punctured a lung.

39:55.143 --> 39:56.133
My mom was there.

39:56.394 --> 39:58.511
She saw me on the ground,
screaming out in pain.

39:58.605 --> 40:01.268
All she said was, "You're not too hurt
to run in the seventh, are you?"

40:03.067 --> 40:04.774
Got a job at Red Lobster after that.

40:05.987 --> 40:06.977
I like that place.

40:07.405 --> 40:10.694
I went to the one in Spokane with my dad
for my 13th birthday.

40:12.035 --> 40:13.992
But then I went back.
And that's what happens.

40:14.746 --> 40:17.204
I started riding for this guy
that made Del look like a good guy.

40:17.916 --> 40:19.077
I mean, a real pervert.

40:19.167 --> 40:20.749
He liked to watch girls taking a piss.

40:21.711 --> 40:23.623
Then there was another horse that spooked.

40:24.756 --> 40:26.418
Threw me into the rail,
and I broke my back.

40:27.300 --> 40:28.916
- Shit.
- It was worse for the horse.

40:29.010 --> 40:30.342
Broke both his forelegs.

40:30.428 --> 40:31.794
Something I'd hardly ever seen before.

40:32.263 --> 40:33.253
Hey, what can I get you?

40:34.098 --> 40:36.135
- Uh, elephant ear.
- All righty.

40:37.352 --> 40:38.263
And then what?

40:38.728 --> 40:40.890
Then I met Del. He lets me ride.

40:44.442 --> 40:45.523
- Thank you, ma'am.
- Thank you.

40:47.695 --> 40:49.061
Sometimes I think I might quit.

40:50.323 --> 40:52.235
There's only so many times
you can fall down, right?

40:54.702 --> 40:56.034
You could go back to Red Lobster.

40:57.830 --> 40:58.741
That I could.

41:06.214 --> 41:07.421
Yeah!

41:14.973 --> 41:15.963
Hey, Bonnie?

41:16.349 --> 41:17.339
What?

41:19.060 --> 41:21.427
I heard someone down by the track

41:21.521 --> 41:24.138
saying that Del runs
his horses into the ground.

41:24.816 --> 41:25.897
You think he'll do that with Pete?

41:26.776 --> 41:30.065
Well, it's true. If Del's broke,
he'll run his horses every two weeks.

41:30.154 --> 41:31.486
Sometimes even once a week.

41:33.199 --> 41:34.189
And is he broke?

41:34.826 --> 41:36.567
He's broke a lot more than he used to be.

41:36.995 --> 41:39.954
We haven't done the fair circuit
in a long while. We're here now, so...

41:42.250 --> 41:43.115
Don't worry about Pete.

41:43.209 --> 41:45.121
He's a Quarter Horse,
so he's got that going for him.

41:45.211 --> 41:46.918
And he's probably been
laid up for a while.

41:48.297 --> 41:50.414
Listen, you can't get attached
to the horse.

41:51.384 --> 41:52.374
Why not?

41:52.760 --> 41:55.548
'Cause you can't think of them as pets.
They're here to race and nothing else.

41:57.473 --> 41:58.964
If they lose too much, they get fired.

42:00.560 --> 42:01.550
Just the way it is.

42:03.730 --> 42:04.937
Come on, let's get going.

42:08.401 --> 42:10.063
<i>This race
is a Quarter Horse event.</i>

42:10.153 --> 42:12.110
<i>Just a 200-yard dash
down the straightaway.</i>

42:12.196 --> 42:13.778
<i>Don't blink or you might miss it.</i>

42:13.865 --> 42:17.074
<i>Here's Bonnie Durand riding
number one, Lean On Pete.</i>

42:18.745 --> 42:19.656
Come on, Pete.

42:19.746 --> 42:21.578
<i>Lean On Pete into gate one
on the inside.</i>

42:45.772 --> 42:48.014
<i>Lean On Pete and Bonnie
broke well down...</i>

42:48.107 --> 42:48.972
Faster, Pete.

42:49.067 --> 42:50.433
- Come on!
- Go, go!

42:53.237 --> 42:55.103
.<i>..but it's all Lean On Pete.</i>

42:56.199 --> 42:58.657
<i>Lean On Pete and Bonnie Durand
hit it with ease.</i>

42:58.743 --> 43:00.609
- We won!
- Yeah.

43:00.703 --> 43:01.693
Did you see?

43:02.246 --> 43:03.236
No.

43:05.333 --> 43:06.824
Holy shit.

43:08.044 --> 43:09.455
- He won, right?
- Yes.

43:17.220 --> 43:18.210
Here.

43:18.638 --> 43:20.049
- Did you get rid of it?
- Yep.

43:21.140 --> 43:23.132
Looks like Rodriguez is gonna
send out a search party.

43:23.226 --> 43:24.342
Don't worry about it.

43:26.354 --> 43:27.890
Is he okay?

43:28.439 --> 43:30.055
Yeah, he just ran faster
than he should have.

43:31.776 --> 43:32.937
What are the tests for?

43:34.403 --> 43:35.814
They test the winner for drugs.

43:36.864 --> 43:37.854
Did Del give him something?

43:38.324 --> 43:40.737
- Is that why he ran fast?
- No. Keep your voice down.

43:44.497 --> 43:45.829
What did you tell him you got rid of?

43:49.669 --> 43:50.659
A buzzer.

43:51.629 --> 43:53.370
- What's that?
- Don't worry, they won't find it.

43:53.464 --> 43:54.545
Yeah, but what is that?

43:54.841 --> 43:56.377
Just gives the horse a little shock.

43:57.426 --> 43:58.416
What kind of shock?

44:00.721 --> 44:01.711
Hi.

44:14.152 --> 44:15.142
We good?

44:16.487 --> 44:17.648
Let's get the fuck out of here.

44:18.865 --> 44:20.527
- See you, Richie.
- All right.

44:24.036 --> 44:27.200
Man, that Rodriguez
is one suspicious son of a bitch.

44:27.540 --> 44:28.781
Huh. I wonder why?

44:41.762 --> 44:42.969
Don't worry, he's fine.

44:50.438 --> 44:51.929
<i>So, what do you think
about all this, Charley?</i>

44:52.356 --> 44:53.346
<i>What do you mean?</i>

44:54.150 --> 44:55.607
<i>You know, working the backside...</i>

44:56.110 --> 44:57.692
surrounded by horse shit.

44:59.197 --> 45:01.063
Being here in the asshole of nowhere.

45:03.492 --> 45:04.858
I like working the horses.

45:08.206 --> 45:09.572
And we need the money, so...

45:09.999 --> 45:14.585
Hey, you should do something else
before there's nothing else you can do.

45:16.214 --> 45:18.046
Shit, I used to like horses,
too, you know.

45:20.259 --> 45:22.626
Now sometimes I feel like
I wanna punch myself in the face

45:22.720 --> 45:24.052
if I ever see a horse again.

45:29.018 --> 45:30.008
Got the good stuff.

45:41.697 --> 45:44.986
I'm okay. I think I'm gonna
make a phone call if that's all right.

45:45.785 --> 45:47.492
Yeah, why don't you go get
something to eat, too?

45:48.204 --> 45:51.038
- I know you must be hungry.
- I just don't have any money.

45:53.459 --> 45:55.200
Well, shit, I could pay you right now.

45:57.213 --> 45:58.203
Are you sure?

45:58.464 --> 46:01.957
Hey, any day I make more than I spend
on these goddamn horses

46:02.051 --> 46:03.337
is a good day in my book.

46:07.598 --> 46:08.588
Bon appÃ©tit.

46:09.934 --> 46:10.924
Thanks.

46:12.019 --> 46:13.009
All right, well...

46:14.146 --> 46:15.136
See you guys later.

46:16.023 --> 46:19.107
- Can you wake him?
<i>- No, he needs his sleep.</i>

46:19.193 --> 46:20.149
All right, but he got my note?

46:20.236 --> 46:21.568
<i>Yes, I told him.</i>

46:21.654 --> 46:23.270
Okay. Yeah, no, as long as he got my...

46:23.364 --> 46:24.275
<i>- Okay, Charley.</i>
- Thank you.

46:33.165 --> 46:34.827
<i>Operator.</i>

46:35.167 --> 46:36.624
Hi, I'm looking for a number.

46:36.711 --> 46:38.668
Um, for Margy Thompson.

46:39.297 --> 46:40.287
<i>Which county?</i>

46:40.673 --> 46:43.131
Yeah, no, she lives
in Rock Springs, Wyoming.

46:45.261 --> 46:46.672
<i>I'm sorry, there's no listing for her.</i>

46:47.179 --> 46:48.169
There's no one at all?

46:48.723 --> 46:49.713
<i>No.</i>

46:50.182 --> 46:51.969
Maybe if you check under Margaret.

46:53.352 --> 46:54.342
<i>Okay.</i>

46:54.937 --> 46:56.053
Can you check that?

46:56.731 --> 46:59.064
<i>Yeah, I'm sorry, nothing's coming up.</i>

46:59.150 --> 47:00.891
Okay. Never mind.

47:06.991 --> 47:09.699
- Here you are, sweetheart.
- Oh, I didn't order that.

47:09.785 --> 47:10.946
That's on the house.

47:11.245 --> 47:12.702
Thank you very much.

47:46.322 --> 47:47.654
He don't look that bad yet.

47:49.116 --> 47:50.732
He looks like
he's walking on nails to me.

47:52.661 --> 47:54.072
You don't think
he's navicular, do you?

47:54.372 --> 47:55.362
I don't know.

47:56.165 --> 47:57.155
I don't think so.

48:01.045 --> 48:02.877
We'll see how he goes down at Grants Pass.

48:04.924 --> 48:06.756
You think
he'll be rested enough by then?

48:06.842 --> 48:10.210
He's gonna have to be.
I'm not wasting my good horses down there.

48:11.680 --> 48:14.889
Tell you one thing, if I had a gun,
I'd probably shoot him right now.

48:15.518 --> 48:16.554
But he just won.

48:17.520 --> 48:18.886
And you raced him too hard.

48:18.979 --> 48:20.595
Listen, kid, things are changing.

48:22.316 --> 48:24.524
The race meet starts soon,
and we're gonna have a lot to do,

48:24.610 --> 48:26.397
so we can't fuck around, you got that?

48:28.072 --> 48:29.483
Let's load up and get back.

48:35.121 --> 48:36.737
Like I said, Charley, he's not a pet.

48:37.373 --> 48:38.409
He's just a horse.

49:17.288 --> 49:18.369
Charley!

49:18.456 --> 49:19.822
- Hey, where's my dad?
- Hey.

49:20.458 --> 49:22.199
We tried calling you at the house.
Where you been?

49:22.293 --> 49:24.080
- Has he gone home?
- Listen, come with me.

49:24.795 --> 49:26.912
- Where the hell is he?
- Um...

49:27.673 --> 49:29.790
Why don't you go have a seat
in his room over here?

49:30.926 --> 49:31.916
Okay.

49:33.679 --> 49:35.591
- Is he with you?
- I'm gonna be right back, okay?

49:35.681 --> 49:36.671
Just give me a minute.

49:49.778 --> 49:50.768
Charley.

49:51.697 --> 49:53.814
I'm really sorry, but he didn't make it.

49:54.658 --> 49:55.694
What do you mean, he didn't make it?

49:55.784 --> 49:58.322
Okay, so that cut that was in his bowel,

49:59.121 --> 50:00.953
there was one that didn't
show up on the X-ray,

50:01.040 --> 50:03.783
and so that became septic.
And then his organs...

50:05.127 --> 50:07.665
- I don't understand.
- Okay. I'm really sorry.

50:11.050 --> 50:15.636
Listen, he wasn't in any pain.
He was asleep when it happened.

50:19.183 --> 50:20.890
You said he was okay two days ago.

50:21.310 --> 50:22.926
Okay, I need you to give me a number
of somebody...

50:23.020 --> 50:24.727
I wouldn't have gone if he wasn't okay.

50:24.813 --> 50:27.180
Charley, listen.
Do you have someone I can call...

50:27.274 --> 50:28.515
You said he was asleep.

50:28.859 --> 50:32.523
- Did he get my note, or was he asleep?
- Um... I'm sorry, Charley,

50:32.738 --> 50:34.479
but I need to call someone for you.

50:36.325 --> 50:38.408
- Just give me a number.
- There is nobody.

50:39.161 --> 50:40.151
Okay.

50:40.955 --> 50:43.197
Okay. Um, well, we can figure this out.

